markers.description: Get the train to Mount Victoria using transportnsw.info.
From the exit of the station head left down Station Street.
Turn right at the Great Western Highway and follow the footpath along it.
At the service station follow the sign to Mount York to the right.
Follow the signs to Lockyers Road along the road.
At the parking area for Berghofers Pass, this walk follow bushtrail the left, to Lockyers Road instead of Lawsons Long Alley.
Instead of going down Lawsons Long Alley, follow the trail that starts parallel to the road to the left.
The trail starts out following a power line, to the trail down the ridge.
At the split in the trail follow the directions down Lockyers Road, away from the power lines.
The trail follow the top of a narrow ridge with intermittent views on both sides.
At the end of the ridge, the trail gradually descends into the valley.
After reaching the bottom, follow the directions to Cox Road to the left or take the detour to the picnic area at the track head.
This short excursion into country NSW may leave you wanting more.
markers.title: Shortest Country Tour
markers.instruction: Visit this location to earn the mystery trophy

markers.description: The picnic area has some tables in the shade and latrines.
Continue the walk by following the direction to Cox Road.
Follow the road along the farm field, until a sign to Mount York veers off to the left down a narrow trail.
The trail gets a little rought, but has many signs pointing the right way.
The walk leads between two farm fields towards Mount York.
Eventually the walking track starts to wind its way steeply up Mount York.
Near the top there are several trails that all lead to the Mount York car park.
Many lookouts suround the car park.
Follow the signs to the car park to find the monument and main lookout.
From the car park follow the walking trail along the main road away from Mount York.
There's a toilet block at the carpark.
Along the way there are several lookouts down side trail to the right of the track.
Make your way out of the park along the main road.
From the intersection with the highway follow the footpath to the left back to Mount Victoria.
Head left down Station Street back to the trains.
Plan your return trip from Mount Victoria at transportnsw.info.
